WEBVTT

00:00:34.722 --> 00:00:38.059
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

00:00:38.143 --> 00:00:40.812
PRESIDENT KANG NORA'S
NEW YEAR PRESS CONFERENCE

00:00:40.895 --> 00:00:44.149
Hello, I'm Kang Nora, the president
of Hanmin Investment &amp; Securities.

00:00:44.232 --> 00:00:45.650
Before I became president,

00:00:45.733 --> 00:00:50.113
I joined Hanmin on September 1, 1997,
as an entry-level employee,

00:00:50.196 --> 00:00:53.116
under my childhood name of Kang Eun-joo.

00:00:53.199 --> 00:00:57.203
Chairman Kang Pil-beom wished for me
to start at the bottom

00:00:57.287 --> 00:01:00.206
and learn alongside ordinary people.

00:01:00.290 --> 00:01:01.583
Well done, sir.

00:01:02.584 --> 00:01:04.627
That's also when I left home

00:01:04.711 --> 00:01:07.922
and moved into the Seoul City Dormitory
for Single Female Workers

00:01:08.006 --> 00:01:10.049
to live with roommates for three months.

00:01:11.926 --> 00:01:15.930
That was when I learned family is about
sharing meals, laughing together,

00:01:16.014 --> 00:01:17.307
and even arguing at times.

00:01:17.891 --> 00:01:22.145
I consider every Hanmin employee
a member of my family.

00:01:45.835 --> 00:01:48.379
Mom, I need to talk to Ms. Hong
briefly before we go.

00:01:50.006 --> 00:01:51.257
Okay.

00:01:56.638 --> 00:01:58.223
Bom, go see what Grandma is up to.

00:01:58.306 --> 00:01:59.140
Okay.

00:02:04.270 --> 00:02:05.521
I want to help too.

00:02:06.606 --> 00:02:08.149
I can do it too.

00:02:10.318 --> 00:02:11.861
You once told us

00:02:13.029 --> 00:02:16.950
that we have no idea how distrustful
and terrifying your father can be.

00:02:19.494 --> 00:02:21.621
We need someone who can stay by his side

00:02:21.704 --> 00:02:23.539
and deceive him until the very end.

00:02:24.749 --> 00:02:26.125
Do you think you can do that?

00:02:36.844 --> 00:02:37.804
Hello?

00:02:37.887 --> 00:02:39.555
Your outfit for the press conference

00:02:39.639 --> 00:02:41.599
is in the women's locker room.

00:03:22.015 --> 00:03:23.766
KANG EUN-JOO

00:03:31.441 --> 00:03:33.443
This is my favorite hairpin.

00:03:34.861 --> 00:03:38.031
This is a secret,
but wearing it gives you strength.

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:41.159
For the sake of Hanmin

00:03:41.242 --> 00:03:43.536
and for the sake of the Hanmin family,

00:03:44.162 --> 00:03:47.749
I will exercise my shareholder rights
in support of Yeouido Pirates.

00:03:47.832 --> 00:03:50.001
What's this now?

00:03:53.755 --> 00:03:55.256
Ms. Song!

00:03:56.632 --> 00:03:57.759
And I know nothing

00:03:57.842 --> 00:04:00.178
about the Swiss borrowed-name account
in my name.

00:04:00.261 --> 00:04:01.929
Please reveal the truth,
National Tax Service!

00:04:07.852 --> 00:04:08.936
Get her!

00:04:11.147 --> 00:04:11.981
Why that little…

00:04:13.149 --> 00:04:14.567
Why, you brat!

00:04:18.196 --> 00:04:19.030
Get her!

00:04:19.113 --> 00:04:20.865
Damn it.

00:04:23.284 --> 00:04:24.494
Get her!

00:04:26.537 --> 00:04:30.249
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

00:04:30.333 --> 00:04:32.960
EPISODE 16: WE OF THE NEW MILLENNIUM

00:04:39.175 --> 00:04:40.259
So

00:04:40.343 --> 00:04:43.679
Kang Nora just double-crossed
the chairman, right?

00:04:43.763 --> 00:04:44.639
Her own dad?

00:04:44.722 --> 00:04:47.141
But what was that
about a Swiss bank account?

00:04:47.225 --> 00:04:50.603
I hear there's 100 billion won
in that Swiss slush fund account.

00:04:50.686 --> 00:04:51.813
-One hundred billion won?
-Seriously?

00:04:53.356 --> 00:04:54.190
One hundred billion won?

00:04:55.566 --> 00:04:57.276
He had all that money…

00:04:59.362 --> 00:05:02.156
yet laid off workers,
saying the company was struggling?

00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:05.785
Damn it.

00:05:07.912 --> 00:05:09.330
I can't talk for long.

00:05:09.414 --> 00:05:11.791
It's all over the news right now.

00:05:11.874 --> 00:05:12.792
Hey,

00:05:13.584 --> 00:05:15.002
if it's all gone to hell,

00:05:15.086 --> 00:05:18.005
let's take what's ours while we can.

00:05:21.884 --> 00:05:24.262
Hanmin's new year press conference today

00:05:24.345 --> 00:05:26.806
was anticipated to celebrate
the official transfer of power

00:05:26.889 --> 00:05:30.977
from Chairman Kang Pil-beom
to his only daughter, President Kang Nora.

00:05:31.060 --> 00:05:32.145
However, at the press conference,

00:05:32.228 --> 00:05:34.230
President Kang delivered
an unexpected announcement

00:05:34.313 --> 00:05:36.691
that left the room in shock.

00:05:36.774 --> 00:05:40.319
I will exercise my shareholder rights
in support of Yeouido Pirates.

00:05:41.195 --> 00:05:44.198
President Kang announced
that she would entrust her stake

00:05:44.282 --> 00:05:46.534
to Yeouido Pirates,
the second-largest shareholder

00:05:46.617 --> 00:05:49.162
which had demanded
the removal of Chairman Kang…

00:05:52.999 --> 00:05:53.916
Sir.

00:05:55.751 --> 00:05:57.879
I think it'd be best for you
to go overseas for a while.

00:05:58.880 --> 00:06:02.383
I'm looking for the earliest flight
out of the country.

00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:04.177
I will gladly escort you.

00:06:04.260 --> 00:06:06.554
No, no.

00:06:06.637 --> 00:06:08.472
I'll need someone

00:06:08.556 --> 00:06:11.809
to stick around to deal with the press
and the police investigation.

00:06:12.351 --> 00:06:14.520
Who else can I trust?

00:06:15.605 --> 00:06:18.566
The only people
who know about the slush funds

00:06:18.649 --> 00:06:21.235
are you and me.

00:06:21.319 --> 00:06:25.489
You should stay in Seoul
and take care of things for now.

00:06:25.573 --> 00:06:28.201
Afterward, we'll reconvene in Switzerland.

00:06:29.076 --> 00:06:32.705
I have to clear out
that Swiss account first.

00:06:32.788 --> 00:06:36.500
So before the police raid us,

00:06:36.584 --> 00:06:37.877
go to the office

00:06:38.461 --> 00:06:41.923
and get rid of anything
that could be incriminating.

00:06:45.885 --> 00:06:46.802
I have always…

00:06:49.472 --> 00:06:51.891
given it my all
for you and the company, sir.

00:06:53.643 --> 00:06:54.518
This time as well,

00:06:55.978 --> 00:06:58.648
I will follow your lead
without asking any questions.

00:06:59.273 --> 00:07:00.149
Good.

00:07:10.243 --> 00:07:12.245
I left my stuffed animals at my office.

00:07:12.328 --> 00:07:14.664
Should I ask the smug trio
to mail them to me?

00:07:14.747 --> 00:07:16.541
As if they'd ever do that for you.

00:07:16.624 --> 00:07:19.252
Come on, but I put on
such a passionate performance.

00:07:19.335 --> 00:07:22.046
Auntie, we all did it together.

00:07:23.756 --> 00:07:26.926
The police weren't charging her
with anything related to Hanmin.

00:07:38.187 --> 00:07:42.275
Ms. Go was suspected of embezzlement
and theft by her former employers

00:07:42.358 --> 00:07:45.069
before she even joined Hanmin.

00:07:45.152 --> 00:07:47.363
So are you saying it's my fault?

00:07:47.446 --> 00:07:50.157
You say whatever you want
and order everyone around.

00:07:50.241 --> 00:07:51.284
Why can't I?

00:07:55.955 --> 00:07:57.248
Auntie, what's wrong with you?

00:07:58.416 --> 00:08:00.126
I'm not like Albert.

00:08:00.751 --> 00:08:02.670
I don't want to be arrested
like Queen Bee.

00:08:09.552 --> 00:08:10.386
Ju-ran.

00:08:11.554 --> 00:08:12.722
It appears the soft-hearted Nora

00:08:13.222 --> 00:08:15.850
has turned on Yeouido Pirates.

00:08:17.059 --> 00:08:18.352
We had great teamwork.

00:08:19.437 --> 00:08:21.981
Chairman Kang and Ms. Song
let their guard down as a result.

00:08:23.608 --> 00:08:25.901
But they won't just stand by and watch.

00:08:27.111 --> 00:08:29.989
Someone keeps calling me,
and I'm pretty sure it's Ms. Song.

00:08:30.573 --> 00:08:31.824
Boy, she's scary.

00:08:33.993 --> 00:08:35.411
Where's President Kang?

00:08:35.494 --> 00:08:36.996
She hasn't come to work, has she?

00:08:37.079 --> 00:08:37.913
She's not picking up either?

00:08:37.997 --> 00:08:41.292
Ma'am, the NTS has requested cooperation
in a tax evasion investigation.

00:08:41.876 --> 00:08:45.212
Prosecutors have also issued
a summons in the slush fund probe.

00:08:47.882 --> 00:08:49.759
Don't respond to them
until there's a directive.

00:08:52.345 --> 00:08:53.220
Ma'am.

00:08:54.263 --> 00:08:56.432
The police just requested
a witness interview.

00:08:56.515 --> 00:08:57.725
The police?

00:08:57.808 --> 00:09:01.145
They said the murder investigation
of Kim I-gyeong from the Songwi Branch

00:09:01.228 --> 00:09:02.563
has been reopened.

00:09:08.861 --> 00:09:14.408
CHAIRMAN KANG PIL-BEOM

00:09:34.553 --> 00:09:36.681
DOMESTIC POLITICIANS' SLUSH FUND LEDGER

00:09:38.933 --> 00:09:40.768
DOMESTIC POLITICIANS' SLUSH FUND LEDGER

00:09:41.352 --> 00:09:43.688
Hey, if it's all gone to hell,

00:09:43.771 --> 00:09:45.898
let's take what's ours while we can.

00:10:04.959 --> 00:10:06.377
It's Song Ju-ran.

00:10:06.460 --> 00:10:08.546
This is an urgent directive
from the chairman.

00:10:09.255 --> 00:10:10.089
How much cash

00:10:11.006 --> 00:10:12.341
do you have on hand?

00:10:19.640 --> 00:10:20.641
Ma'am.

00:10:20.725 --> 00:10:23.894
I've reserved two tickets
for a flight that leaves tonight.

00:10:23.978 --> 00:10:25.980
They're under
the chairman's name and yours.

00:10:26.063 --> 00:10:27.273
You can cancel one.

00:10:27.356 --> 00:10:30.067
The chairman won't be leaving.

00:10:51.297 --> 00:10:52.548
Where are you off to?

00:10:53.048 --> 00:10:54.592
To run an errand for the chairman.

00:10:55.217 --> 00:10:56.844
What are you doing here?

00:10:56.927 --> 00:10:59.263
I came to help you,

00:10:59.346 --> 00:11:00.973
just like how you protect the chairman.

00:11:02.183 --> 00:11:03.517
Let's go. I'll give you a ride.

00:11:04.602 --> 00:11:05.436
It's fine.

00:11:06.979 --> 00:11:08.731
You should lie low for a while.

00:11:09.607 --> 00:11:10.524
I'll be in touch.

00:11:13.235 --> 00:11:15.196
I said I'll give you a ride.

00:11:52.983 --> 00:11:55.027
It was just as you said.

00:11:57.238 --> 00:11:59.198
How do you know the chairman?

00:12:00.241 --> 00:12:01.742
Ms. Song.

00:12:02.952 --> 00:12:04.245
All this time,

00:12:04.328 --> 00:12:06.914
I'm sure you thought

00:12:07.581 --> 00:12:09.583
you were running the whole show

00:12:09.667 --> 00:12:13.629
as you relayed orders between him and me.

00:12:14.922 --> 00:12:15.923
But I…

00:12:17.258 --> 00:12:20.469
don't even trust my own flesh and blood.

00:12:21.470 --> 00:12:25.349
So how could I have

00:12:26.183 --> 00:12:28.102
trusted you alone…

00:12:29.853 --> 00:12:32.231
and vested you with full authority?

00:12:34.984 --> 00:12:35.985
I've devoted

00:12:37.444 --> 00:12:38.862
every fiber of my being

00:12:39.655 --> 00:12:41.282
to working for you and Hanmin.

00:12:42.408 --> 00:12:43.450
It has been

00:12:44.159 --> 00:12:45.869
thirty whole years.

00:12:49.123 --> 00:12:51.875
Even when he enticed me
to steal the slush fund together,

00:12:51.959 --> 00:12:53.836
I stayed by your side, sir.

00:12:55.087 --> 00:12:56.547
You must believe me.

00:12:57.464 --> 00:13:00.926
After stealing the company's reserve fund,

00:13:01.010 --> 00:13:03.429
she planned to leave
the country alone tonight.

00:13:04.471 --> 00:13:05.514
How dare you!

00:13:10.853 --> 00:13:12.730
Ms. Song Ju-ran.

00:13:16.275 --> 00:13:17.359
Thank you…

00:13:19.653 --> 00:13:21.363
for all your hard work over the years.

00:13:28.329 --> 00:13:29.204
Sir.

00:13:30.789 --> 00:13:31.832
Chairman.

00:13:32.833 --> 00:13:33.834
Sir!

00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:38.505
Chairman!

00:13:54.271 --> 00:13:56.315
The prosecution
has resumed its investigation

00:13:56.398 --> 00:13:58.359
into Hanmin's Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

00:13:58.442 --> 00:14:01.862
The prosecution initially identified
Chief of Staff Song Ju-ran

00:14:01.945 --> 00:14:03.822
as a key figure
in the slush fund allegations,

00:14:03.906 --> 00:14:06.992
but the investigation has stalled,
with her whereabouts still unknown.

00:14:07.076 --> 00:14:09.828
Ms. Song was often referred to
as Chairman Kang's shadow

00:14:09.912 --> 00:14:14.166
and reportedly oversaw his secret accounts
at home and abroad.

00:14:14.249 --> 00:14:15.209
SEOUL SOUTHERN DISTRICT COURT

00:14:15.292 --> 00:14:17.961
MARCH, 1998: FIRST TRIAL
FOR KANG'S SLUSH FUND EMBEZZLEMENT CASE

00:14:40.109 --> 00:14:42.277
Any lucky signs in your dream last night?

00:14:43.445 --> 00:14:44.863
I couldn't sleep a wink.

00:14:45.864 --> 00:14:48.325
It took way too long to get here.

00:14:48.409 --> 00:14:49.451
Gosh.

00:14:56.750 --> 00:14:57.835
Right,

00:14:58.419 --> 00:15:00.421
so if you really wanted
to go after Hanmin,

00:15:00.504 --> 00:15:03.757
you should've called me in
after securing concrete evidence.

00:15:09.513 --> 00:15:10.347
What's with him?

00:15:11.807 --> 00:15:14.476
We're lucky he was assigned this case.

00:15:15.519 --> 00:15:18.731
Not only was he jumped that night,
but he was also banished to Tongyeong.

00:15:18.814 --> 00:15:20.065
I hear that jerkface prosecutor

00:15:20.149 --> 00:15:23.736
also harbors a mighty grudge
against Chairman Kang.

00:15:23.819 --> 00:15:24.737
I see.

00:15:32.745 --> 00:15:36.081
Ms. Hong, please briefly explain
how this evidence

00:15:36.165 --> 00:15:37.708
came into your possession.

00:15:38.333 --> 00:15:40.961
While investigating Hanmin's slush fund,

00:15:41.045 --> 00:15:43.547
the late President Kang Myeong-hwi
reached out to me.

00:15:44.048 --> 00:15:46.717
He was supposed to hand over
the slush fund ledger,

00:15:47.926 --> 00:15:51.263
but he met his untimely death
in a questionable car accident,

00:15:51.346 --> 00:15:53.766
and the whistleblower
who compiled the ledger

00:15:53.849 --> 00:15:55.517
disappeared around that time.

00:15:56.393 --> 00:15:58.812
In order to find
the whistleblower and the ledger,

00:15:58.896 --> 00:16:00.522
I went undercover at Hanmin

00:16:00.606 --> 00:16:02.399
and carried out
an unofficial investigation.

00:16:02.483 --> 00:16:06.195
I acquired it through Ms. Go Bok-hee,
the late president's former assistant.

00:16:08.822 --> 00:16:09.656
That is all.

00:16:10.240 --> 00:16:11.116
The defense

00:16:11.700 --> 00:16:13.410
may begin questioning the witness.

00:16:22.795 --> 00:16:23.921
Ms. Hong,

00:16:24.505 --> 00:16:26.340
you were an inspector at the FSS

00:16:26.423 --> 00:16:28.717
when you took a job at Hanmin
under a false identity.

00:16:28.801 --> 00:16:30.094
Is that not an unlawful act?

00:16:30.177 --> 00:16:33.097
The undercover employment
was an inevitable step

00:16:33.180 --> 00:16:34.932
in continuing the slush fund probe.

00:16:35.015 --> 00:16:36.642
You claim it was a slush fund probe.

00:16:36.725 --> 00:16:40.646
Yet after you resigned,
you established "Yeouido Pirates,"

00:16:40.729 --> 00:16:44.274
an investment trust company,
to buy up Hanmin stocks, correct?

00:16:44.358 --> 00:16:45.400
Yes, that's correct.

00:16:45.484 --> 00:16:47.111
Was it to seize management control?

00:16:47.945 --> 00:16:50.197
It was to take part
in the company's management.

00:16:50.280 --> 00:16:54.118
I also wished to prevent the company
from a foreign acquisition.

00:16:54.201 --> 00:16:55.953
And where did you obtain the funds

00:16:56.036 --> 00:16:57.079
to purchase said shares?

00:16:59.915 --> 00:17:04.044
Shouldn't you be asking your client
about the source of those funds?

00:17:07.172 --> 00:17:09.466
That money was sourced from
Hanmin's slush fund

00:17:09.550 --> 00:17:11.760
recorded in the slush fund ledger.

00:17:11.844 --> 00:17:12.886
The slush fund?

00:17:22.437 --> 00:17:23.814
Your Honor.

00:17:23.897 --> 00:17:27.484
Ms. Hong was the party who initiated
Hanmin's management control dispute.

00:17:27.568 --> 00:17:30.070
Her claim that the money recorded
in the ledger was a slush fund

00:17:30.154 --> 00:17:32.281
is nothing more than a unilateral claim.

00:17:32.364 --> 00:17:35.075
More importantly, who exactly prepared

00:17:35.576 --> 00:17:37.536
the ledger in question?

00:17:47.462 --> 00:17:49.256
I will decline to answer that question

00:17:49.339 --> 00:17:51.133
to ensure the whistleblower's safety.

00:17:51.758 --> 00:17:55.095
So there's a ledger,
but we don't know who prepared it?

00:17:55.596 --> 00:17:57.931
Isn't it possible
that the ledger was fabricated

00:17:58.015 --> 00:18:01.018
to justify the hostile takeover
and to portray the funds

00:18:01.101 --> 00:18:02.769
as slush money?

00:18:02.853 --> 00:18:04.521
Could this be fabricated evidence?

00:18:04.605 --> 00:18:05.898
It is not.

00:18:07.232 --> 00:18:08.901
Let me be clear,

00:18:09.401 --> 00:18:12.696
I have no knowledge of any slush funds.

00:18:14.656 --> 00:18:18.827
I've never put together or even seen

00:18:18.911 --> 00:18:20.996
a slush fund ledger.

00:18:22.247 --> 00:18:27.002
Once the person who prepared
the mysterious ledger is identified,

00:18:27.085 --> 00:18:29.630
it will become clear as day

00:18:29.713 --> 00:18:33.300
who exactly is lying here.

00:18:37.304 --> 00:18:39.139
I, Kang Pil-beom…

00:18:41.225 --> 00:18:44.394
have only ever spoken the truth.

00:18:55.239 --> 00:18:57.157
We have something prepared,

00:18:57.241 --> 00:18:58.909
but we'll need some time.

00:19:07.709 --> 00:19:10.170
We'll take a 15-minute recess.

00:19:25.519 --> 00:19:27.187
Chairman Kang is doing that on purpose.

00:19:27.271 --> 00:19:28.814
He knows I can't speak up.

00:19:29.731 --> 00:19:31.942
Stop being so stubborn.

00:19:32.025 --> 00:19:33.110
Why can't you tell them?

00:19:33.193 --> 00:19:34.820
Just tell them who Yehppee is.

00:19:34.903 --> 00:19:37.531
Why do you refuse to identify them?

00:19:37.614 --> 00:19:40.325
I promised Yehppee
that I'd keep their secret.

00:19:40.909 --> 00:19:41.994
I can't break that promise.

00:19:42.077 --> 00:19:44.288
You're going to let this
slip through your fingers?

00:19:47.749 --> 00:19:50.043
Say something, President Shin.

00:19:50.627 --> 00:19:53.213
If you were just going to
sit there silently all day,

00:19:53.714 --> 00:19:55.799
you should've gone to a park
and sat on a bench.

00:19:56.383 --> 00:19:57.551
Go on.

00:19:58.343 --> 00:19:59.886
Who wrote the ledger?

00:19:59.970 --> 00:20:01.138
Can't you reach out to them?

00:20:01.221 --> 00:20:02.848
Yehppee ignores my calls.

00:20:03.682 --> 00:20:05.350
We got him hard evidence.

00:20:05.434 --> 00:20:08.729
We've set the stage well enough,
so it's up to the jerkface prosecutor now.

00:20:10.605 --> 00:20:11.440
Wait.

00:20:12.357 --> 00:20:14.901
Man, seriously? That's all you got?

00:20:14.985 --> 00:20:16.236
You are beyond frustrating.

00:20:16.320 --> 00:20:17.654
Wait, Hong!

00:20:18.530 --> 00:20:20.699
Am I the only one
who doesn't know who Yehppee is?

00:20:20.782 --> 00:20:21.867
I don't either.

00:20:22.367 --> 00:20:23.660
Me neither.

00:20:23.744 --> 00:20:24.578
"Yehppee"?

00:20:25.454 --> 00:20:27.247
So why was I the only one called out?

00:20:34.504 --> 00:20:35.422
Your Honor.

00:20:36.048 --> 00:20:38.508
I'd like to call an additional witness
to the stand.

00:20:39.885 --> 00:20:41.345
Why is this witness necessary?

00:20:42.137 --> 00:20:45.390
This witness's testimony is essential
to establishing the facts.

00:20:45.474 --> 00:20:48.685
Wouldn't that violate
the defendant's right to a defense?

00:20:48.769 --> 00:20:50.771
The defense had
also requested this witness.

00:20:50.854 --> 00:20:53.690
He is already in attendance
in the courtroom.

00:20:58.278 --> 00:20:59.363
Is it me?

00:20:59.946 --> 00:21:00.864
I don't think so.

00:21:00.947 --> 00:21:02.074
No, right?

00:21:02.157 --> 00:21:04.743
We'll allow the witness's examination
as an exception.

00:21:04.826 --> 00:21:06.536
However, please ensure
that defense counsel

00:21:06.620 --> 00:21:09.456
is given ample opportunity
for cross-examination.

00:21:09.539 --> 00:21:10.874
Yes, Your Honor.

00:21:10.957 --> 00:21:14.544
Formerly with Hanmin's head office
and author of the slush fund ledger,

00:21:14.628 --> 00:21:15.629
we call Mr. Bang Jin-mok.

00:22:25.907 --> 00:22:29.703
"I swear to tell the truth
and nothing but the truth,

00:22:29.786 --> 00:22:31.121
to testify truthfully,

00:22:31.204 --> 00:22:34.374
and conceal nothing,
in accordance with my conscience."

00:22:34.833 --> 00:22:36.668
"Witness, Bang Jin-mok."

00:22:40.005 --> 00:22:41.423
Mr. Bang.

00:22:42.257 --> 00:22:43.383
This ledger

00:22:44.009 --> 00:22:45.719
was written by you, correct?

00:22:45.802 --> 00:22:47.512
Yes, I did.

00:22:47.596 --> 00:22:49.014
For what purpose did you write it?

00:22:49.598 --> 00:22:51.558
At President Kang Myeong-hwi's urging,

00:22:52.225 --> 00:22:55.353
I documented it to condemn
Chairman Kang Pil-beom's slush fund

00:22:55.437 --> 00:22:57.439
and to ensure
a brighter future for Hanmin.

00:23:00.066 --> 00:23:01.818
Could President Kang Myeong-hwi

00:23:01.902 --> 00:23:05.197
have commissioned the ledger
in an effort to oust his father,

00:23:05.280 --> 00:23:07.782
Chairman Kang Pil-beom,
and take control of Hanmin?

00:23:08.992 --> 00:23:10.744
I do not believe so.

00:23:10.827 --> 00:23:12.621
That's your speculation.

00:23:14.289 --> 00:23:16.583
Aren't you speculating as well?

00:23:17.083 --> 00:23:18.668
The dead can't speak up.

00:23:20.670 --> 00:23:24.549
Was that ledger truly compiled
when President Kang Myeong-hwi was alive?

00:23:24.633 --> 00:23:27.886
Are you certain it wasn't fabricated
after the control dispute began?

00:23:28.470 --> 00:23:30.472
How can you prove that?
There's only one ledger--

00:23:30.555 --> 00:23:32.265
There isn't just one.

00:23:35.060 --> 00:23:36.102
There are 13 in total.

00:23:40.440 --> 00:23:41.566
Did he say 13?

00:23:44.736 --> 00:23:47.197
Hanmin was my first job,

00:23:47.280 --> 00:23:50.784
and my seniors taught me
the fundamentals of corporate life.

00:23:50.867 --> 00:23:53.328
"Doubt everything, verify everything,

00:23:53.411 --> 00:23:55.538
and always keep a backup."

00:23:55.622 --> 00:23:57.249
There were multiple backups?

00:23:58.500 --> 00:23:59.918
Twelve more, at that?

00:24:01.461 --> 00:24:04.089
I left the company last December
when the IMF crisis struck

00:24:04.172 --> 00:24:05.966
and restructuring began.

00:24:06.633 --> 00:24:10.178
My twelfth backup is hidden in the ceiling
of the Risk Management office

00:24:10.262 --> 00:24:13.348
at Hanmin's head office building,
where I used to work.

00:24:14.140 --> 00:24:15.976
What? Where?

00:24:22.107 --> 00:24:22.941
Yehppee!

00:24:27.696 --> 00:24:28.571
At the time,

00:24:29.614 --> 00:24:33.618
Yeouido Pirates had no involvement
in the management of Hanmin.

00:24:33.702 --> 00:24:36.079
And after my exit last December,

00:24:36.162 --> 00:24:38.373
I've never set foot in the head office.

00:24:49.676 --> 00:24:50.510
I was…

00:24:51.720 --> 00:24:52.721
very scared.

00:24:54.055 --> 00:24:55.348
There were even times

00:24:55.432 --> 00:24:58.768
when I regretted ever getting involved.

00:25:00.353 --> 00:25:01.187
However,

00:25:03.189 --> 00:25:05.900
I didn't want my courage

00:25:06.901 --> 00:25:07.736
and…

00:25:10.655 --> 00:25:11.656
the effort

00:25:13.158 --> 00:25:14.159
of my former colleagues

00:25:15.785 --> 00:25:19.622
to be forever in vain.

00:25:22.459 --> 00:25:25.670
Even if you claim
the ledger was fabricated…

00:25:27.881 --> 00:25:29.674
I can prove otherwise.

00:25:52.697 --> 00:25:53.990
Thanks.

00:25:57.869 --> 00:26:00.413
Is this why you refused
to return to the company?

00:26:00.497 --> 00:26:01.998
This needed to be settled first.

00:26:02.582 --> 00:26:04.584
So you're not entirely against going back?

00:26:04.667 --> 00:26:07.629
Why do you care?
You don't work for Hanmin anymore.

00:26:08.213 --> 00:26:12.384
Will Inspector Hong Keum-bo
be returning to the FSS now?

00:26:13.218 --> 00:26:14.886
Who says they'd even take me back?

00:26:15.845 --> 00:26:17.555
I bet they already cleared out your desk.

00:26:18.723 --> 00:26:22.352
With that ledger in your hand,
you stole all those slush funds.

00:26:22.435 --> 00:26:24.229
You have to take responsibility.

00:26:24.312 --> 00:26:26.606
I'm going to file a reinstatement lawsuit.

00:26:27.190 --> 00:26:30.693
I'll prove that the investigation
was related to my work, no matter what.

00:26:30.777 --> 00:26:32.946
You can't prove that by yourself.

00:26:35.323 --> 00:26:37.242
I wouldn't have gone through this trouble

00:26:37.325 --> 00:26:38.993
if Yehppee had been more cooperative.

00:26:43.623 --> 00:26:45.542
I'll cooperate this time.

00:26:46.376 --> 00:26:47.210
I promise.

00:26:50.130 --> 00:26:51.756
Call me if you ever need anything.

00:26:56.302 --> 00:26:58.596
There's a lot left here. You drink it.

00:26:59.764 --> 00:27:00.598
I'm off.

00:27:17.740 --> 00:27:19.200
Did you ask the investigative team?

00:27:19.784 --> 00:27:21.286
I asked discreetly,

00:27:22.370 --> 00:27:26.040
and they said Chairman Kang
is still denying all allegations.

00:27:26.124 --> 00:27:27.292
He claims he knows nothing,

00:27:27.792 --> 00:27:31.254
that it was all Song Ju-ran's doing
behind his back.

00:27:31.796 --> 00:27:34.591
That's nonsense.
He's just trying to pin it all on her.

00:27:34.674 --> 00:27:36.593
Of course, it's nonsense.

00:27:36.676 --> 00:27:41.264
That's why the investigative team
is scrambling to find Song Ju-ran.

00:27:41.347 --> 00:27:43.600
If she doesn't come out of hiding,

00:27:43.683 --> 00:27:46.269
it may be difficult to prove
Chairman Kang's charges.

00:27:46.936 --> 00:27:49.230
But there's no record
of her flying out of the country.

00:27:50.190 --> 00:27:51.733
That means she's still in the country.

00:27:52.901 --> 00:27:55.028
Or maybe she left by boat?

00:27:56.905 --> 00:28:00.575
Didn't Chairman Kang seem
a bit too calm during the trial?

00:28:01.159 --> 00:28:02.577
Like he had something up his sleeve?

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:04.954
With even the politicians'
slush funds exposed,

00:28:05.038 --> 00:28:06.498
there's no one left to help him.

00:28:08.666 --> 00:28:11.002
Let's look at it
from Chairman Kang's perspective.

00:28:12.170 --> 00:28:15.798
Ms. Song was the only one
who knew every detail of his slush fund.

00:28:16.633 --> 00:28:19.594
If Ms. Song, who knows too much
about the slush fund, is gone…

00:28:20.845 --> 00:28:22.597
What if he could make her disappear?

00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:24.641
It would certainly raise suspicions,

00:28:24.724 --> 00:28:26.684
but he could avoid a guilty verdict?

00:28:31.189 --> 00:28:32.398
Damn bastard…

00:28:37.737 --> 00:28:40.573
HANMIN'S OUTSTANDING WOMEN EMPLOYEES

00:28:41.950 --> 00:28:44.327
WOMAN IN HER 20S FOUND DEAD
IN CHUNGSEO RESERVOIR

00:29:00.134 --> 00:29:01.678
Prosecutor, it's Hong Keum-bo.

00:29:02.887 --> 00:29:04.681
Do you want some help finding Song Ju-ran?

00:29:07.892 --> 00:29:08.768
Sir,

00:29:08.852 --> 00:29:12.146
DNA was found under the victim
Kim I-gyeong's fingernails.

00:29:12.230 --> 00:29:14.524
Once a suspect is identified,
we can run a DNA test--

00:29:14.607 --> 00:29:17.151
It's been almost three months
since the body was found,

00:29:17.235 --> 00:29:18.778
and we still don't have a suspect.

00:29:19.654 --> 00:29:21.614
Just rule it as a suicide already.

00:29:21.698 --> 00:29:23.074
But it wasn't a suicide!

00:29:24.367 --> 00:29:26.870
We have the plate number
of the van she got into.

00:29:26.953 --> 00:29:27.787
Bro.

00:29:27.871 --> 00:29:31.583
If she got into the back seat,
that means someone else was driving.

00:29:31.666 --> 00:29:34.961
That was a stolen plate, remember?

00:29:35.044 --> 00:29:37.297
Why are you being so stubborn about this?

00:29:37.380 --> 00:29:39.257
Man, you're so damn frustrating.

00:29:40.133 --> 00:29:41.843
-Wait, bro!
-Whatever. Leave me alone!

00:29:41.926 --> 00:29:43.052
We have work to do!

00:29:49.684 --> 00:29:50.518
Hello?

00:29:53.479 --> 00:29:54.397
Who is this?

00:29:55.773 --> 00:29:58.484
There's a shop called Horang Auto Repair
on Seoul's outskirts.

00:29:59.694 --> 00:30:02.822
It's run by a man in his late forties
named Bong Dal-su.

00:30:03.865 --> 00:30:05.742
And according to a reliable source,

00:30:05.825 --> 00:30:08.244
he's somehow related
to Kim I-gyeong's death.

00:30:08.328 --> 00:30:09.162
Sir.

00:30:12.624 --> 00:30:15.293
It matches the plate seen
on the day she disappeared.

00:30:16.544 --> 00:30:17.837
SEOUL 6
K 3307

00:30:19.714 --> 00:30:21.549
OFFICE

00:30:27.555 --> 00:30:29.974
This is the evidence we collected
from Horang Auto Repair Shop.

00:30:30.683 --> 00:30:32.685
It appears Bong Dal-su kept them

00:30:33.186 --> 00:30:34.604
as souvenirs of his crimes.

00:30:35.563 --> 00:30:37.065
Hanmin President Kang Myeong-hwi's wallet…

00:30:42.028 --> 00:30:44.405
and Songwi Branch teller
Kim I-gyeong's wallet were found.

00:30:44.989 --> 00:30:46.449
Aside from those two victims,

00:30:46.532 --> 00:30:49.202
the others don't appear
to be connected to Hanmin.

00:30:50.370 --> 00:30:51.329
Just a moment.

00:30:52.538 --> 00:30:53.957
Can I take a look at this?

00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:54.874
Sure.

00:31:06.678 --> 00:31:08.513
CHEONGSAN ACCOUNTING FIRM

00:31:10.473 --> 00:31:12.558
YUN JAE-UNG

00:31:12.642 --> 00:31:17.105
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
YUN JAE-UNG

00:31:21.901 --> 00:31:23.236
…and audit report wordplay.

00:31:23.319 --> 00:31:24.320
HANMIN FINANCIAL AUDIT

00:31:24.404 --> 00:31:25.405
It's all unacceptable.

00:31:25.488 --> 00:31:27.115
-Mr. Yun.
-Yes, sir?

00:31:27.198 --> 00:31:28.366
Sorry, Keum-bo.

00:31:28.449 --> 00:31:31.494
I'll persuade him to do the right thing.

00:31:32.412 --> 00:31:35.248
Mr. Yun, the accountant
who was being investigated by the police,

00:31:35.331 --> 00:31:37.917
committed suicide
by jumping from his apartment building

00:31:38.001 --> 00:31:39.043
around 3 p.m. today.

00:31:51.681 --> 00:31:54.100
If Bong Dal-su doesn't show up today…

00:31:54.642 --> 00:31:57.103
Then we'll continue waiting tomorrow.

00:32:01.315 --> 00:32:02.400
He's on the wanted list.

00:32:02.483 --> 00:32:04.986
We appreciate the tip,
but it's our job to investigate--

00:32:05.069 --> 00:32:06.237
He's here. There.

00:32:35.725 --> 00:32:36.768
Go on. Follow him.

00:32:36.851 --> 00:32:38.519
-Maintain distance.
-Yes, ma'am.

00:32:38.603 --> 00:32:40.104
-Hurry up.
-Yes, sir.

00:33:04.921 --> 00:33:07.256
Wait, why is he going into that house?

00:33:07.340 --> 00:33:08.466
Do you recognize it?

00:33:08.549 --> 00:33:10.760
It's Chairman Kang Pil-beom's place.

00:33:11.260 --> 00:33:13.221
Hey, let's request a warrant first.

00:33:15.681 --> 00:33:17.350
I'll get off nearby.

00:33:17.934 --> 00:33:20.603
My goodness, you didn't need to.

00:33:21.771 --> 00:33:22.772
Ta-da.

00:33:27.735 --> 00:33:28.778
Ta-da!

00:33:28.861 --> 00:33:31.823
I heard you're supposed to eat tofu
when you get out of prison

00:33:31.906 --> 00:33:32.740
to purify your soul.

00:33:32.824 --> 00:33:34.575
I haven't gone to prison yet.

00:33:34.659 --> 00:33:36.536
I'm being investigated without detention.

00:33:37.120 --> 00:33:40.623
I guess I'll have a bite
since you went through the trouble.

00:33:41.999 --> 00:33:43.084
Is there no soy sauce?

00:33:43.918 --> 00:33:44.752
No.

00:33:48.923 --> 00:33:49.757
Hello?

00:33:50.341 --> 00:33:51.217
Nora,

00:33:51.759 --> 00:33:53.636
do you still have the keys
to Chairman Kang's house?

00:33:54.512 --> 00:33:55.346
Yes.

00:33:55.429 --> 00:33:56.931
Come meet me right now.

00:33:57.515 --> 00:33:58.641
What is it?

00:34:22.206 --> 00:34:24.250
The chairman has made a decision.

00:34:28.171 --> 00:34:29.797
I don't want to do this either.

00:34:32.091 --> 00:34:33.634
You understand, right?

00:34:45.688 --> 00:34:48.441
This is why you should've listened to me.

00:34:50.276 --> 00:34:51.819
I said we should just take the money.

00:34:56.532 --> 00:34:57.533
Damn it.

00:34:59.327 --> 00:35:00.453
The chairman has already

00:35:01.204 --> 00:35:02.747
left this palace of a house.

00:35:04.874 --> 00:35:05.791
The whole world is

00:35:06.500 --> 00:35:08.211
buzzing about the slush fund.

00:35:08.878 --> 00:35:10.922
No one will care if you disappear.

00:35:13.174 --> 00:35:15.301
People can be so cruel.

00:35:15.801 --> 00:35:16.636
Right?

00:35:22.308 --> 00:35:24.852
I'll be back
after I park the car in the garage.

00:35:58.344 --> 00:35:59.470
Let's get out of here.

00:36:04.183 --> 00:36:05.518
You can't die like this.

00:36:17.405 --> 00:36:18.239
Let's hurry.

00:36:37.591 --> 00:36:38.801
Now,

00:36:39.760 --> 00:36:42.013
none of you can make it out alive.

00:36:45.933 --> 00:36:47.059
Go and hide down there.

00:36:47.143 --> 00:36:48.978
-What about you?
-I'll be fine. Hurry.

00:36:50.604 --> 00:36:51.856
Let's go for now.

00:36:51.939 --> 00:36:52.773
Where are you going?

00:36:53.524 --> 00:36:54.567
Hey, stop.

00:36:55.109 --> 00:36:56.319
Why you little…

00:37:12.001 --> 00:37:12.877
Damn you.

00:37:22.428 --> 00:37:23.512
Damn it. Let go of me.

00:37:36.901 --> 00:37:37.735
Damn it.

00:37:41.405 --> 00:37:43.157
You're not going anywhere.

00:37:48.079 --> 00:37:49.038
What's your deal?

00:37:49.121 --> 00:37:51.165
Why? Tell me.

00:37:51.248 --> 00:37:52.666
Why?

00:37:52.750 --> 00:37:53.584
Damn it!

00:37:54.460 --> 00:37:55.294
You!

00:38:05.763 --> 00:38:06.722
Damn it.

00:38:31.205 --> 00:38:35.584
The unidentified DNA
found under Kim I-gyeong's fingernails…

00:38:39.255 --> 00:38:41.674
matches yours, Bong Dal-su.

00:38:43.634 --> 00:38:45.719
Did you keep those wallets in your drawer

00:38:45.803 --> 00:38:47.721
as souvenirs after you killed the victims?

00:38:48.264 --> 00:38:50.099
Then what about Hanmin President
Kang Myeong-hwi?

00:38:53.727 --> 00:38:56.188
You didn't do it alone.
You know Song Ju-ran, don't you?

00:38:56.981 --> 00:39:00.484
The Hanmin Chief of Staff you confined
in Chairman Kang's basement.

00:39:04.447 --> 00:39:05.322
Everything

00:39:05.906 --> 00:39:07.825
was under Song Ju-ran's orders.

00:39:10.202 --> 00:39:11.412
It's true.

00:39:15.332 --> 00:39:16.625
That's not true, is it?

00:39:16.709 --> 00:39:18.377
There's someone above her.

00:39:19.420 --> 00:39:20.671
Chairman Kang Pil-beom.

00:39:21.255 --> 00:39:22.173
Where is he?

00:39:48.115 --> 00:39:49.283
Why aren't you eating?

00:39:49.366 --> 00:39:52.495
You need to recover
so you can get investigated by the police

00:39:52.995 --> 00:39:54.747
and stand trial.

00:39:56.832 --> 00:39:58.209
Did you come all this way

00:39:59.376 --> 00:40:00.419
for a thank you?

00:40:02.671 --> 00:40:03.839
At the end of the day…

00:40:05.883 --> 00:40:07.801
you only found me to use me.

00:40:08.636 --> 00:40:10.638
You're half-right and half-wrong.

00:40:12.598 --> 00:40:15.768
I wanted you to be fairly judged
and punished accordingly.

00:40:16.477 --> 00:40:17.770
I never wanted you dead.

00:40:18.979 --> 00:40:20.314
It's not because it's you,

00:40:21.148 --> 00:40:22.858
but because nobody deserves that.

00:40:24.693 --> 00:40:27.821
For all the female employees
who admired you

00:40:28.364 --> 00:40:31.200
but were exploited and discarded by you…

00:40:33.285 --> 00:40:35.579
I hope you live with remorse
from this day on.

00:41:13.450 --> 00:41:16.495
Ms. Song, the chief of staff at Hanmin
who covered up the murder

00:41:16.579 --> 00:41:19.540
of a female branch employee as a suicide,
has been arrested.

00:41:19.623 --> 00:41:23.502
After DNA found on the victim's body
matched that of Mr. Bong,

00:41:23.586 --> 00:41:25.754
an acquaintance of Ms. Song
from her hometown,

00:41:25.838 --> 00:41:30.009
the police reclassified the case
from suicide to homicide.

00:41:30.092 --> 00:41:33.804
Ms. Song had previously been identified
as a key figure

00:41:33.887 --> 00:41:37.141
and the so-called "key man"
in the Hanmin slush fund investigation.

00:41:37.224 --> 00:41:39.310
So I'm banned from leaving the country

00:41:40.185 --> 00:41:42.688
starting at noon tomorrow?

00:41:42.771 --> 00:41:44.106
Not today, right?

00:41:45.733 --> 00:41:46.567
All right.

00:41:47.568 --> 00:41:48.861
I understand.

00:41:48.944 --> 00:41:51.488
Come visit me in Switzerland sometime.

00:41:52.615 --> 00:41:55.659
I'll make sure to repay you then.

00:41:56.285 --> 00:41:57.119
Good.

00:41:57.202 --> 00:41:58.412
Oh jeez.

00:41:58.495 --> 00:41:59.371
Chairman.

00:42:00.122 --> 00:42:01.665
Have you been hiding here this whole time?

00:42:03.042 --> 00:42:06.086
How did you even know about this place?

00:42:06.170 --> 00:42:07.880
I know you, honey.

00:42:08.380 --> 00:42:09.506
Even when we were together,

00:42:09.590 --> 00:42:12.176
you always came to this VIP ward
whenever things got tough.

00:42:14.136 --> 00:42:16.680
You saw the news
about Song Ju-ran's arrest, right?

00:42:17.431 --> 00:42:18.974
What did I tell you?

00:42:19.058 --> 00:42:20.517
She totally screwed you over.

00:42:21.518 --> 00:42:23.354
-Where's Nora?
-Who knows?

00:42:23.437 --> 00:42:24.980
That brat won't even answer my calls.

00:42:26.106 --> 00:42:28.776
What in the world happened
after I moved out?

00:42:33.113 --> 00:42:35.199
-In-ja.
-Yes, honey?

00:42:40.079 --> 00:42:41.288
Do you

00:42:42.081 --> 00:42:43.540
want to come with me?

00:42:45.042 --> 00:42:45.876
What?

00:43:34.216 --> 00:43:35.384
We've arrived, sir.

00:43:38.387 --> 00:43:39.221
Oh, right.

00:43:42.891 --> 00:43:44.810
Hey, where did she go?

00:43:45.561 --> 00:43:46.395
Hey!

00:43:47.146 --> 00:43:48.230
What in the world?

00:43:53.902 --> 00:43:54.862
What the…

00:43:55.612 --> 00:43:56.447
You!

00:43:57.448 --> 00:43:58.282
You're…

00:43:59.199 --> 00:44:00.409
A NEW POLICE FORCE COMMITTED TO THE PEOPLE

00:44:00.492 --> 00:44:01.869
Wait a minute.

00:44:01.952 --> 00:44:03.746
What's going on here?

00:44:05.164 --> 00:44:06.206
Choi In-ja!

00:44:06.290 --> 00:44:07.374
What?

00:44:07.458 --> 00:44:08.584
Why are you calling me?

00:44:09.752 --> 00:44:12.588
Mr. Kang Pil-beom,
I'm a former Miss Korea.

00:44:12.671 --> 00:44:15.758
The one-time Best New Actress nominee
at the Golden Dragon Film Awards,

00:44:15.841 --> 00:44:17.092
Choi In-ja.

00:44:17.176 --> 00:44:18.427
I'm not the kind of woman

00:44:18.510 --> 00:44:20.596
who'd live in fear,
hiding out with a fugitive.

00:44:47.664 --> 00:44:49.750
-Hey.
-The chairman asked you for his passport

00:44:49.833 --> 00:44:51.168
and his emergency cash, right?

00:44:51.251 --> 00:44:53.378
I found the passport and cash.

00:44:53.462 --> 00:44:54.379
And the plane ticket?

00:44:54.463 --> 00:44:57.841
Tell him the flight departs
from Kimpo Airport at 11 p.m. tonight

00:44:57.925 --> 00:44:59.676
and that you'll pick up the tickets there.

00:44:59.760 --> 00:45:02.095
Departing from Kimpo Airport
at 11 p.m. tonight.

00:45:02.179 --> 00:45:03.013
Got it.

00:45:03.096 --> 00:45:05.682
Your final destination
will be the police station.

00:45:07.851 --> 00:45:09.978
Babe, I got this.

00:45:13.732 --> 00:45:15.067
Choi In-ja!

00:45:16.652 --> 00:45:17.611
Why you…

00:45:21.406 --> 00:45:22.324
Damn it!

00:45:25.994 --> 00:45:27.329
-Chairman Kang Pil-beom.
-Let go!

00:45:27.412 --> 00:45:28.705
We'd appreciate your cooperation.

00:45:29.289 --> 00:45:30.791
-My goodness.
-Let's go.

00:45:31.500 --> 00:45:32.751
I can't believe this.

00:45:33.794 --> 00:45:34.628
Let go of me!

00:45:37.548 --> 00:45:39.424
This is unbelievable.

00:45:43.178 --> 00:45:44.388
Thank you, ma'am.

00:45:46.139 --> 00:45:48.892
A man who makes you ashamed
that you ever lived with him

00:45:48.976 --> 00:45:50.477
deserves to face judgment.

00:46:02.072 --> 00:46:02.906
Come here.

00:46:22.009 --> 00:46:24.553
BONAK POLICE STATION

00:46:33.604 --> 00:46:34.605
Thank you.

00:46:34.688 --> 00:46:37.691
YUN JAE-UNG'S PERSONAL EFFECTS

00:46:59.671 --> 00:47:02.799
CHEONGSAN ACCOUNTING FIRM
YUN JAE-UNG

00:47:06.219 --> 00:47:08.305
RESIDENT REGISTRATION CARD
YUN JAE-UNG

00:47:51.515 --> 00:47:52.349
Today,

00:47:53.350 --> 00:47:56.436
I went to the places I used to go
with Uncle Myeong-hwi.

00:47:57.688 --> 00:48:00.023
The movie theater, record shop,

00:48:00.524 --> 00:48:02.025
basketball court, places like that.

00:48:03.735 --> 00:48:05.070
I wanted to commemorate him.

00:48:06.613 --> 00:48:07.447
Oh, right.

00:48:09.157 --> 00:48:10.742
I'm going to use his wallet now.

00:48:12.661 --> 00:48:14.746
I'm glad to see you holding up.

00:48:16.123 --> 00:48:19.626
Director Yun had a really tough day today.

00:48:20.669 --> 00:48:22.462
Learning his little brother's death

00:48:22.546 --> 00:48:24.297
wasn't a suicide but a homicide…

00:48:30.721 --> 00:48:32.222
So you called me to check in on me?

00:48:33.807 --> 00:48:34.725
But

00:48:34.808 --> 00:48:36.560
I'd rather live like this than live a lie.

00:48:38.019 --> 00:48:39.938
Uncle Myeong-hwi would want this for me.

00:48:44.317 --> 00:48:45.819
If it weren't for you,

00:48:46.528 --> 00:48:48.488
none of this would've been possible.

00:48:48.989 --> 00:48:50.157
Thank you.

00:48:51.742 --> 00:48:52.784
That thank you…

00:48:54.161 --> 00:48:55.787
sounds too much like a goodbye.

00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:27.778
You should go.

00:49:28.945 --> 00:49:30.655
I'm going to stay for a bit longer.

00:49:32.908 --> 00:49:33.784
Okay then.

00:49:53.136 --> 00:49:54.012
Goodbye…

00:49:56.014 --> 00:49:57.015
Hong Jang-mi.

00:50:04.231 --> 00:50:07.526
After the chairman was arrested,
customer complaints have only escalated.

00:50:07.609 --> 00:50:09.319
SET YOUR MIND AT EASE WITH HANMIN
NEW HIGH-YIELD INVESTMENT PRODUCT!

00:50:09.402 --> 00:50:12.364
The branch manager ran out yesterday
and never returned.

00:50:12.447 --> 00:50:13.865
He didn't come into work today.

00:50:14.950 --> 00:50:16.952
What if the company goes under?

00:50:17.035 --> 00:50:18.829
What are you doing, Ms. Kim?

00:50:19.454 --> 00:50:22.749
A few angry customers,
and this place will be a mess again.

00:50:23.250 --> 00:50:25.627
Yeah, I heard
even the head office has given up.

00:50:25.710 --> 00:50:26.962
We should still do our jobs.

00:50:28.088 --> 00:50:29.840
The company hasn't gone under yet.

00:50:35.178 --> 00:50:36.388
MS. KIM AT MAGANG BRANCH

00:50:36.471 --> 00:50:37.973
KIM MI-SOOK AT MAGANG BRANCH

00:50:39.099 --> 00:50:40.100
MS. LEE AT CHEONGAN BRANCH

00:50:40.183 --> 00:50:41.226
LEE HE-GYEONG AT CHEONGAN BRANCH

00:50:42.727 --> 00:50:43.562
MS. PARK AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

00:50:43.645 --> 00:50:45.063
PARK MYEONG-HUI AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

00:50:45.146 --> 00:50:46.356
MS. KIM AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

00:50:46.439 --> 00:50:48.316
KIM MI-GYEONG AT BUKJEONGWON BRANCH

00:50:49.401 --> 00:50:50.777
KIM HYEON-SUK AT YEONGPO BRANCH

00:50:50.861 --> 00:50:52.279
LEE GYEONG-SUK AT YEONGPO BRANCH

00:50:52.362 --> 00:50:54.364
Kang Pil-beom,
the former chairman of Hanmin,

00:50:54.447 --> 00:50:57.284
who was indicted on charges
of embezzlement and breach of duty,

00:50:57.367 --> 00:50:58.910
was found guilty in his second trial.

00:50:58.994 --> 00:51:02.414
Kang expressed his intention
to file an immediate appeal.

00:51:02.497 --> 00:51:04.207
Meanwhile, Yeouido Pirates will be

00:51:04.291 --> 00:51:07.460
selling its shares to the Hanmin Employee
Stock Ownership Association.

00:51:07.544 --> 00:51:10.714
This share sale is to foster
shared growth with employees

00:51:10.797 --> 00:51:12.382
while strengthening shareholder value.

00:51:12.465 --> 00:51:15.135
All slush funds amassed
by former Chairman Kang

00:51:15.218 --> 00:51:17.053
will be returned to Hanmin.

00:51:17.554 --> 00:51:22.267
And Yeouido Pirates will disband
after a new head of Hanmin is appointed.

00:51:30.942 --> 00:51:31.776
Mr. Cha.

00:51:31.860 --> 00:51:33.194
Why are you acting weird…

00:51:34.779 --> 00:51:36.197
Why are you delivering the coffee?

00:51:36.281 --> 00:51:37.157
Ms. Hong.

00:51:37.908 --> 00:51:39.326
Ms. Hong Keum-bo.

00:51:39.409 --> 00:51:41.411
That was a discriminatory comment.

00:51:42.037 --> 00:51:42.954
Me?

00:51:43.705 --> 00:51:46.082
I don't think I should be hearing that
from you, of all people.

00:51:49.127 --> 00:51:52.297
I'll leave you to your meeting then.

00:52:17.489 --> 00:52:19.032
To get straight to the point,

00:52:19.115 --> 00:52:21.201
many people in the company believe

00:52:21.284 --> 00:52:24.204
that you'd be the right choice
to lead Hanmin at this time.

00:52:25.705 --> 00:52:27.040
I can't do that.

00:52:27.666 --> 00:52:30.085
Given my involvement
in the creation of the slush fund,

00:52:30.627 --> 00:52:31.503
I'm not qualified.

00:52:33.463 --> 00:52:35.799
I'm sure there are

00:52:36.549 --> 00:52:39.219
many career executives eyeing the role.

00:52:39.302 --> 00:52:40.637
There certainly is a lot,

00:52:41.221 --> 00:52:43.848
but there's a strong backlash
after the DK Ventures incident.

00:52:50.939 --> 00:52:53.358
Where could we possibly find
someone who understands

00:52:53.441 --> 00:52:55.485
Hanmin's current situation
with your financial acumen,

00:52:55.568 --> 00:52:58.071
leadership skills,
and even moral integrity?

00:53:08.665 --> 00:53:12.794
There is one person
who has delivered consistent results

00:53:12.877 --> 00:53:14.045
over a long tenure,

00:53:14.129 --> 00:53:17.674
and had only marginal involvement
in the former chairman's slush fund.

00:53:18.299 --> 00:53:20.593
He also possesses keen management skills,

00:53:20.677 --> 00:53:23.096
and I think he might be a good fit.

00:53:27.100 --> 00:53:29.144
I hope it's not who I think it is.

00:53:29.227 --> 00:53:32.689
Sometimes, the position makes the leader.

00:53:51.416 --> 00:53:52.625
I have three questions.

00:53:52.709 --> 00:53:54.878
Why did you help us
at the shareholders' meeting?

00:53:56.504 --> 00:53:57.672
Because I wanted to follow

00:53:57.756 --> 00:53:59.424
my heart and not my head.

00:54:01.259 --> 00:54:02.218
What are you saying?

00:54:05.221 --> 00:54:07.640
As soon as Hong Keum-bo
stepped up to fight,

00:54:07.724 --> 00:54:10.268
it was obvious
that she'd be fighting a losing battle.

00:54:11.686 --> 00:54:14.814
My head told me
to side with Chairman Kang,

00:54:14.898 --> 00:54:16.274
but my heart, for some reason…

00:54:19.569 --> 00:54:21.529
wanted Hong Keum-bo to win.

00:54:24.574 --> 00:54:25.408
Satisfied?

00:54:32.707 --> 00:54:34.459
It was political instinct.

00:54:35.168 --> 00:54:37.712
Do you think I got to where I am
by just sitting around?

00:54:39.839 --> 00:54:41.633
Is it true that you weren't

00:54:41.716 --> 00:54:43.760
directly involved
in the slush fund creation?

00:54:45.136 --> 00:54:47.597
From Myeong-hwi, Mr. So,
and even Mr. Bang…

00:54:47.680 --> 00:54:50.558
I was the one who got stabbed in the back!

00:54:55.438 --> 00:54:56.272
Last question.

00:54:56.815 --> 00:54:59.234
Would you be interested
in an 11-month interim CEO position?

00:54:59.818 --> 00:55:00.860
Interim…

00:55:03.780 --> 00:55:04.823
CEO?

00:55:04.906 --> 00:55:07.367
Of course, it won't be my decision alone.

00:55:08.660 --> 00:55:10.662
A quick refusal would be great.

00:55:10.745 --> 00:55:12.413
"The position makes the leader."

00:55:13.540 --> 00:55:14.541
Does it, really?

00:55:19.254 --> 00:55:20.088
CEO?

00:55:23.758 --> 00:55:24.676
Oh my.

00:55:24.759 --> 00:55:26.886
NOTICE OF APPOINTMENT

00:55:26.970 --> 00:55:27.804
POSITION: CEO

00:55:27.887 --> 00:55:29.430
NAME: CHA JUNG-IL

00:55:29.931 --> 00:55:32.225
HANMIN INVESTMENT &amp; SECURITIES

00:55:32.308 --> 00:55:35.728
Let's make the employee payroll account
our flagship product.

00:55:35.812 --> 00:55:38.231
Let's offer them interest as banks do.

00:55:38.314 --> 00:55:40.692
We'll approach it
as comprehensive wealth management.

00:55:41.484 --> 00:55:45.029
I'd also like to see a campaign
targeting entry-level staff and new hires.

00:55:45.822 --> 00:55:48.825
This year's customer count is a bit--

00:55:49.409 --> 00:55:50.535
Hey!

00:55:58.209 --> 00:56:00.587
"The position makes the leader."

00:56:00.670 --> 00:56:01.629
Does it, really?

00:56:02.255 --> 00:56:03.214
Ms. Hong.

00:56:08.011 --> 00:56:10.221
Let's try to be more careful next time.

00:56:11.598 --> 00:56:13.308
Let's try…

00:56:13.808 --> 00:56:15.894
to make sure this doesn't happen again.

00:56:18.396 --> 00:56:19.230
You may leave.

00:56:19.314 --> 00:56:20.773
"THE POSITION MAKES THE LEADER…
DOES IT, REALLY?"

00:56:20.857 --> 00:56:23.526
"THE POSITION MADE THE LEADER!"
CHA JUNG-IL

00:56:59.395 --> 00:57:02.023
I'm here
for a lunch appointment with Nora.

00:57:02.857 --> 00:57:03.900
So am I.

00:57:06.611 --> 00:57:08.029
You haven't figured it out yet?

00:57:08.112 --> 00:57:10.657
She clearly set this up so we could meet.

00:57:24.504 --> 00:57:27.131
Ms. Kang Nora ordered it
when she made the reservation.

00:57:41.896 --> 00:57:43.982
Cha Jung-il becoming
the president of Hanmin?

00:57:46.150 --> 00:57:47.318
He won by luck.

00:57:47.402 --> 00:57:48.236
Dad.

00:57:48.903 --> 00:57:50.780
You still want it
after everything that happened?

00:57:52.323 --> 00:57:54.742
Son, if everyone grew from experience,

00:57:54.826 --> 00:57:56.494
this world would be full of saints.

00:58:12.427 --> 00:58:13.761
The steak is good.

00:58:20.518 --> 00:58:21.644
Open up.

00:58:29.277 --> 00:58:30.820
This steak is good indeed.

00:58:37.493 --> 00:58:38.870
The thing with money is…

00:58:40.204 --> 00:58:41.831
Never mind. Let's eat.

00:58:44.167 --> 00:58:46.085
ULLALA CHICKEN

00:58:46.169 --> 00:58:47.879
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

00:58:48.463 --> 00:58:50.173
Cheers, Ms. Go!

00:58:50.256 --> 00:58:51.591
DETAINED IN THE END!
CURRENTLY IN PRISON

00:58:54.844 --> 00:58:56.638
How's your new place, Big Al and Mr. Lee?

00:58:56.721 --> 00:58:59.015
It's a rooftop apartment,
so it has a nice view.

00:59:00.183 --> 00:59:02.226
You have enough money for a decent place.

00:59:02.310 --> 00:59:04.020
Big Al, you received your dividends,

00:59:04.103 --> 00:59:05.480
and Mr. Lee, you got your severance pay.

00:59:05.563 --> 00:59:08.483
I drained my savings to buy
my favorite video rental place.

00:59:08.566 --> 00:59:10.151
That screenplay I've been putting off…

00:59:10.985 --> 00:59:12.362
It's time to give it a final scene.

00:59:14.030 --> 00:59:16.115
I also started a game company.

00:59:16.699 --> 00:59:18.534
And I used up my severance to buy land.

00:59:18.618 --> 00:59:20.370
Am I the only one nervous about this?

00:59:20.453 --> 00:59:22.330
Where's the land?

00:59:23.289 --> 00:59:24.123
In Pangyo.

00:59:26.250 --> 00:59:29.337
It's mostly rice fields
and orchards right now,

00:59:29.420 --> 00:59:31.506
but just as Yeouido became
the center of finance,

00:59:31.589 --> 00:59:33.091
I'll grow my game company

00:59:33.174 --> 00:59:35.510
and turn that area into a leading IT hub!

00:59:40.723 --> 00:59:41.974
Good luck. Yeah.

00:59:42.058 --> 00:59:43.976
You never know what the future holds.

00:59:44.060 --> 00:59:46.020
Well, should we cheers to that?

00:59:47.438 --> 00:59:49.273
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

00:59:58.574 --> 01:00:00.243
ULLALA CHICKEN

01:00:00.326 --> 01:00:01.577
Your parents must be worried.

01:00:02.412 --> 01:00:03.246
It's fine.

01:00:03.955 --> 01:00:07.125
Compared to being fired from my first job
and living in exile at the library,

01:00:07.208 --> 01:00:09.377
I'm at least making a decent living now.

01:00:11.963 --> 01:00:13.840
I'm leaving Korea tomorrow.

01:00:15.466 --> 01:00:16.884
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

01:00:17.385 --> 01:00:18.594
You should at least say goodbye.

01:00:18.678 --> 01:00:21.180
I just didn't want it to be a farewell.

01:00:22.557 --> 01:00:23.933
You never know what the future holds.

01:00:27.270 --> 01:00:29.313
Thank you for all your hard work.

01:00:30.732 --> 01:00:33.359
It was my way of apologizing for the past,

01:00:33.443 --> 01:00:34.694
though I'm sure you already knew.

01:00:38.698 --> 01:00:40.450
I used to think

01:00:40.533 --> 01:00:43.494
fate and sincerity
were nothing but romantic excuses.

01:00:44.245 --> 01:00:47.832
But reuniting with you
and working alongside you

01:00:48.791 --> 01:00:50.084
gave those words meaning.

01:00:52.462 --> 01:00:53.629
Thank you for giving me

01:00:54.839 --> 01:00:55.840
a chance.

01:01:19.280 --> 01:01:20.615
JEONGBOM KINDERGARTEN GRADUATION

01:01:20.698 --> 01:01:22.033
FEBRUARY, 1999

01:01:22.116 --> 01:01:25.495
We will now present
the Cleaning Champion Award.

01:01:25.578 --> 01:01:27.205
Seo Won-jong!

01:01:29.540 --> 01:01:30.833
They're so cute.

01:01:32.752 --> 01:01:34.420
Who knew I'd end up
at a kindergarten graduation?

01:01:34.504 --> 01:01:35.379
I know, right?

01:01:36.380 --> 01:01:38.090
I present you with your award.

01:01:38.174 --> 01:01:40.384
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

01:01:43.095 --> 01:01:44.972
Our Bom is all grown up now.

01:01:45.056 --> 01:01:46.516
She'll be in grade school in the spring.

01:01:46.599 --> 01:01:47.850
Elementary school.

01:01:48.392 --> 01:01:50.394
We should be celebrating, not criticizing.

01:01:50.478 --> 01:01:52.313
I only just got out of the slammer.

01:01:52.814 --> 01:01:54.065
I'll cut you slack this time.

01:01:54.649 --> 01:01:56.651
Wait, am I the only one with flowers?

01:01:56.734 --> 01:01:59.070
I made Bom's favorite dessert.

01:01:59.153 --> 01:02:00.238
Ta-da!

01:02:09.038 --> 01:02:12.041
Auntie Nora went to France
to pursue her love for food

01:02:12.124 --> 01:02:15.586
and returned as a pastry chef.

01:02:17.255 --> 01:02:18.589
I prepared cash.

01:02:18.673 --> 01:02:20.007
No muss, no fuss.

01:02:20.967 --> 01:02:22.760
Big Auntie Bok-hee said

01:02:22.844 --> 01:02:26.639
she did just fine in prison,
managing backdoor money

01:02:26.722 --> 01:02:29.600
for inmates, guards, and even the warden.

01:02:30.977 --> 01:02:33.396
Now, she secretly operates
a private detective agency

01:02:33.479 --> 01:02:35.606
under the guise of a hair salon

01:02:35.690 --> 01:02:38.484
to help her clients find
their husbands' hidden slush funds.

01:02:41.362 --> 01:02:42.280
Welcome.

01:02:42.363 --> 01:02:45.199
She said the real Auntie Jang-mi
is her business partner.

01:02:45.283 --> 01:02:47.702
-For women in their thirties--
-Twenties.

01:02:48.995 --> 01:02:50.496
-Sorry?
-I'm in my twenties.

01:02:51.747 --> 01:02:52.707
Can you do it?

01:02:52.790 --> 01:02:53.666
Sure.

01:02:55.459 --> 01:02:56.836
Who's looking to divorce?

01:02:56.919 --> 01:02:58.296
Me. That's me.

01:02:58.379 --> 01:03:00.006
Listen carefully.

01:03:00.089 --> 01:03:01.716
You must check if he's hiding any money

01:03:01.799 --> 01:03:05.386
before you throw
those divorce papers at your husband.

01:03:05.469 --> 01:03:07.555
Bank accounts,
insurance policies, and land deeds!

01:03:19.233 --> 01:03:21.319
This award goes
to everyone's greatest friend.

01:03:21.402 --> 01:03:23.487
The Friendship Award goes to

01:03:23.571 --> 01:03:24.530
Kim Bom!

01:03:28.117 --> 01:03:29.619
Way to go, Bom!

01:03:29.702 --> 01:03:30.995
So cool, Bom!

01:03:31.078 --> 01:03:32.622
So cute, Bom!

01:03:34.540 --> 01:03:35.708
The Friendship Award

01:03:35.791 --> 01:03:38.336
is awarded to everyone's greatest friend,
Kim Bom.

01:03:38.920 --> 01:03:39.837
Congratulations.

01:03:50.264 --> 01:03:51.599
Hey, Mom!

01:03:52.683 --> 01:03:55.937
As for my mom, Ms. Kim Mi-sook…

01:03:56.020 --> 01:03:58.814
This is so damn annoying.

01:03:58.898 --> 01:04:00.691
I told you that's what I want.

01:04:00.775 --> 01:04:03.402
Who are you to tell me no?
Is this your money?

01:04:03.486 --> 01:04:04.487
Is it?

01:04:08.157 --> 01:04:09.492
Who the hell are you to--

01:04:13.955 --> 01:04:14.789
Sir.

01:04:14.872 --> 01:04:16.415
Please refrain
from using abusive language.

01:04:17.166 --> 01:04:19.585
What? Who are you?

01:04:20.169 --> 01:04:23.339
If you continue to cause fear,
I will report you to the police.

01:04:28.511 --> 01:04:30.304
She attends an online university

01:04:30.388 --> 01:04:33.057
and still works at Hanmin,

01:04:33.140 --> 01:04:35.434
now as an assistant manager.

01:04:48.364 --> 01:04:49.657
This dormitory

01:04:49.740 --> 01:04:52.785
will officially cease operations
on February 8, 1999.

01:04:52.868 --> 01:04:55.955
We thank all residents
from the bottom of our hearts,

01:04:56.038 --> 01:04:58.874
and we sincerely wish you all
health and luck

01:04:58.958 --> 01:05:00.418
throughout the four seasons.

01:05:00.501 --> 01:05:02.461
They must've already moved everything out.

01:05:02.545 --> 01:05:05.089
Too bad, I wanted to look inside.

01:05:05.172 --> 01:05:07.591
I'm sure the RA would
give us permission if we asked.

01:05:08.801 --> 01:05:10.594
Should I ask the security guard?

01:05:12.680 --> 01:05:15.224
We know the gate
isn't the only way inside.

01:05:46.297 --> 01:05:47.506
Are you okay?

01:05:47.590 --> 01:05:49.300
Let's go. Come on.

01:05:55.765 --> 01:05:58.184
Gosh, these halls feel so empty now.

01:06:35.387 --> 01:06:37.640
It's nice to meet you. I'm Hong Jang-mi.

01:06:38.724 --> 01:06:40.309
I turned 20

01:06:40.893 --> 01:06:41.852
this year.

01:06:43.020 --> 01:06:43.854
Here.

01:06:43.938 --> 01:06:44.897
Hong Jang-mi.

01:06:44.980 --> 01:06:48.609
As of today, you're officially recognized
as a resident of Room 301.

01:06:49.819 --> 01:06:50.820
Thanks.

01:06:50.903 --> 01:06:53.531
Gather around, Room 301.

01:06:53.614 --> 01:06:54.657
Ta-da.

01:06:54.740 --> 01:06:56.283
Living under the same roof

01:06:56.367 --> 01:06:58.577
and sharing meals makes us family.

01:07:05.000 --> 01:07:06.418
Operation Seodongyo is a go.

01:07:06.502 --> 01:07:07.628
Help me out, ladies.

01:07:08.546 --> 01:07:10.756
FEMALE EMPLOYEE… FIRED… HONG JANG-MI…

01:07:10.840 --> 01:07:12.258
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

01:07:19.098 --> 01:07:20.349
Mommy.

01:07:28.774 --> 01:07:30.276
Good job!

01:07:30.359 --> 01:07:31.694
Ta-da.

01:07:32.194 --> 01:07:33.571
What are beeper numbers?

01:07:33.654 --> 01:07:36.699
If you're ever in trouble,
you just need to call one of the aunties.

01:07:37.283 --> 01:07:39.326
We're Bom's aunties!

01:07:39.410 --> 01:07:40.286
Bom.

01:07:45.082 --> 01:07:47.042
What are we going to do?

01:07:50.921 --> 01:07:52.548
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere?

01:07:52.631 --> 01:07:53.883
Tell me you're okay first!

01:07:53.966 --> 01:07:54.884
I'm fine.

01:07:57.386 --> 01:07:59.430
I thought you'd be worried
about the money,

01:07:59.513 --> 01:08:01.182
but you worried about me first.

01:08:01.265 --> 01:08:02.391
Seriously?

01:08:03.100 --> 01:08:05.019
You can call her big sis.

01:08:05.102 --> 01:08:06.729
Everyone knows she's old.

01:08:09.190 --> 01:08:10.232
Mommy!

01:08:10.316 --> 01:08:11.317
Bom!

01:08:13.360 --> 01:08:14.862
Bom, I'm so sorry.

01:08:28.292 --> 01:08:30.753
Let's all take a picture together.

01:08:46.936 --> 01:08:49.396
It is the Year of the White Metal Dragon.

01:08:49.480 --> 01:08:52.942
The dragon has long been
a symbol of great hope and success,

01:08:53.025 --> 01:08:56.487
and there is understandably great hope
for the year ahead.

01:08:56.570 --> 01:09:00.241
Leaders worldwide have shared messages
to commemorate the millennium,

01:09:00.324 --> 01:09:04.161
stressing the importance
of global cooperation and progress.

01:09:08.207 --> 01:09:09.875
Winning the reinstatement case

01:09:11.168 --> 01:09:12.544
won't be easy.

01:09:12.628 --> 01:09:15.297
Will you start the new millennium
on a sour note?

01:09:15.381 --> 01:09:16.465
However…

01:09:19.051 --> 01:09:21.720
I'm considering proposing
a conditional reinstatement.

01:09:23.639 --> 01:09:26.308
It appears you're here
to represent the organization.

01:09:27.434 --> 01:09:28.394
Fine, I'll play along.

01:09:30.562 --> 01:09:33.232
This reinstatement lawsuit
seeks formal recognition

01:09:33.315 --> 01:09:35.526
of my employee status
during my undercover work in 1997.

01:09:35.609 --> 01:09:37.403
I do not wish to negotiate it as a term.

01:09:39.029 --> 01:09:40.322
Why the sudden business tone?

01:09:41.448 --> 01:09:43.325
You said you wanted to come back, Hong.

01:09:43.409 --> 01:09:46.578
I'm trying to justify that
for both you and the organization.

01:09:49.164 --> 01:09:50.332
I'll hear you out for now.

01:09:58.340 --> 01:10:01.385
These bodies were found along highways
and in the hills in South Gyeongsang.

01:10:01.468 --> 01:10:02.636
VICTIM 1: PARK MI-JEONG
YOU &amp; ME INSURANCE AGENT

01:10:02.720 --> 01:10:05.973
The police are treating it
as a serial murder case for now.

01:10:06.056 --> 01:10:07.141
But the thing is,

01:10:07.224 --> 01:10:10.185
all of the victims
have one thing in common.

01:10:11.395 --> 01:10:12.313
Insurance.

01:10:13.105 --> 01:10:14.189
Insurance.

01:10:15.691 --> 01:10:17.109
Two insurance agents,

01:10:17.192 --> 01:10:19.194
an insurance policyholder,

01:10:19.278 --> 01:10:20.696
and a beneficiary.

01:10:20.779 --> 01:10:23.240
They're all through You &amp; Me Insurance.

01:10:23.324 --> 01:10:26.785
They were also supposed to testify for us
in the insurance fraud case.

01:10:30.581 --> 01:10:31.498
So?

01:10:32.041 --> 01:10:36.170
Would you go undercover again
and help carry out the investigation?

01:10:38.047 --> 01:10:39.256
Again?

01:10:39.340 --> 01:10:40.924
You want me to do that nonsense again?

01:10:41.008 --> 01:10:43.677
"Nonsense"? Come on now.

01:10:43.761 --> 01:10:46.305
You did great,
and you'll do great again this time.

01:10:46.805 --> 01:10:48.682
Let's put your skills to use again.

01:10:48.766 --> 01:10:50.434
It'll be just for three months.

01:10:50.517 --> 01:10:53.520
You don't have to worry about
appearances this time.

01:10:53.604 --> 01:10:56.857
Going undercover as a 20-year-old
last time was ridiculous.

01:10:57.441 --> 01:10:58.400
This time,

01:10:58.484 --> 01:11:01.195
you can be a 36-year-old
insurance agent or…

01:11:01.278 --> 01:11:02.946
Anyway, you've got many options.

01:11:03.030 --> 01:11:04.114
If you do well,

01:11:04.198 --> 01:11:06.617
you can choose the division you want
at the head office.

01:11:07.493 --> 01:11:10.079
The governor said whatever you want!

01:11:15.167 --> 01:11:16.085
But why me?

01:11:24.802 --> 01:11:27.179
That doesn't suit you at all.

01:11:29.807 --> 01:11:31.225
What about this?

01:11:31.308 --> 01:11:32.559
Sure. Knock yourself out.

01:11:33.852 --> 01:11:35.646
I need to look intimidating.

01:11:37.231 --> 01:11:38.482
Hong Keum-bo.

01:11:38.565 --> 01:11:41.360
Forget all the trouble,
and join me on a trip to LA.

01:11:42.236 --> 01:11:44.530
Queen Bee, I'm going to borrow this too.

01:11:44.613 --> 01:11:46.865
At least tell me
what kind of business trip it is.

01:11:47.950 --> 01:11:49.410
Visit me in Busan sometime.

01:11:49.493 --> 01:11:50.828
We can go to Gwangalli together.

01:11:51.412 --> 01:11:52.287
Busan?

01:11:53.705 --> 01:11:54.623
Gwangalli?

01:11:56.583 --> 01:12:00.587
GWANGALLI

01:12:00.671 --> 01:12:02.005
YOU &amp; ME INSURANCE
WILL TAKE FULL RESPONSIBILITY

01:12:19.857 --> 01:12:22.860
A certified black belt in martial arts,
a young male police officer,

01:12:22.943 --> 01:12:24.611
and two robust male employees

01:12:25.362 --> 01:12:26.697
were all knocked out.

01:12:27.656 --> 01:12:28.574
Hong,

01:12:29.283 --> 01:12:30.909
win the battle of nerves first.

01:12:31.452 --> 01:12:32.911
You know those ladies have some nerve.

01:12:35.539 --> 01:12:36.457
You got this!

01:12:58.061 --> 01:12:59.563
But you know,

01:12:59.646 --> 01:13:01.982
I really thought you'd get it.

01:13:02.065 --> 01:13:04.485
I thought so too.

01:13:04.568 --> 01:13:05.819
This year is a bust.

01:13:06.862 --> 01:13:09.281
Bust? Do you know how much
she made in bonuses this month?

01:13:09.364 --> 01:13:11.200
Yeah, that's right.

01:13:11.700 --> 01:13:14.036
-As if I wouldn't know.
-Hold on a second.

01:13:14.119 --> 01:13:18.165
I hear the new branch manager
is coming from the Seoul head office.

01:13:18.248 --> 01:13:19.750
-She's a Seoulite?
-Yeah.

01:13:20.751 --> 01:13:22.669
She's probably some frail little thing.

01:13:22.753 --> 01:13:25.005
-Like me?
-Stop it already.

01:13:25.088 --> 01:13:27.132
You should make that into a package.

01:13:27.216 --> 01:13:29.009
Listen, you…

01:13:29.676 --> 01:13:31.637
-Stop it.
-You're unbelievable.

01:13:35.557 --> 01:13:36.725
What's your deal, kid?

01:13:36.808 --> 01:13:38.060
She might not be a kid.

01:13:40.354 --> 01:13:43.023
Hello, I'm Hong Keum-bo.

01:13:43.106 --> 01:13:43.941
I'm…

01:13:45.901 --> 01:13:47.694
the new bookkeeper here.

01:13:50.239 --> 01:13:51.657
Gosh, you scared us!

01:13:52.366 --> 01:13:53.784
Come here.

01:13:53.867 --> 01:13:56.161
You're the new bookkeeper?
It's nice to meet you.

01:13:57.204 --> 01:14:00.749
My goodness, I thought…

01:14:03.168 --> 01:14:05.420
I look forward to working with you.

01:14:07.756 --> 01:14:09.633
You are such a pretty young lady!

01:14:20.644 --> 01:14:24.690
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:14:25.732 --> 01:14:27.568
UNDERCOVER MISS HONG

01:14:28.068 --> 01:14:31.863
SPECIAL THANKS TO SHIN YU-NA
AND PARK JUNG-PYO FOR THEIR APPEARANCES

01:14:31.947 --> 01:14:35.367
Hanmin is, in name and reality,
a first-rate company that has led…

01:14:37.244 --> 01:14:38.495
Act natural.

01:14:51.800 --> 01:14:54.511
If you ever run that mouth
about Mi-sook again,

01:14:55.512 --> 01:14:56.972
I will end you.

01:14:57.639 --> 01:15:00.142
By the will of the heavens,
it ended up in my hands.

01:15:01.310 --> 01:15:02.936
Good work, everyone.

01:15:05.731 --> 01:15:06.565
-"All of you"?
-"All of you"?

01:15:07.566 --> 01:15:10.611
My twelfth backup is hidden in the ceiling
of the Risk Management office

01:15:10.694 --> 01:15:13.780
at Hanmin's head office building,
where I used to work.

01:15:13.864 --> 01:15:15.032
Where?

01:15:18.410 --> 01:15:20.287
Yehppee!

01:15:20.370 --> 01:15:25.375
Subtitle translation by: Justin S. Kim